<p>Cennydd Bowles is a digital product designer and writer based in Brighton, UK. He speaks at design and user experience conferences across the globe and is a regular mentor of new design talent. He writes for <a href="http://www.cennydd.co.uk/">his popular blog</a> and <a href="http://www.cennydd.co.uk/writing/">influential design publications</a>, and is the author of <i><a href="http://undercoverux.com/">Undercover User Experience Design</a></i> and the upcoming <i>Designing the Wider Web</i>. Pronounce his name Ken-ith, with a hard <em>th</em> to rhyme with ‘with’.</p>
<p>You can find him on Twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/cennydd">@Cennydd</a>.</p>